PIEOmONT
AUTOMATIC
OXYGEN
SYSTEM
The higher altitudes
at which this aircraft operates require prompt
use of the automatic oxygen system in case of any sudden change
in cabin pressure. Should a decompression occur,
oxygen masks
will drop down automatically. Take nearest mask and promptly place
over nose and mouth and lean back in your seat.
BRACE
POSITIONS
In an emergency
situation your
Flight Attendant
may request you
to assume one of
the Bracing
Positions shown.
INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE OF SEAT BELTS
LIFT TO UNFASTEN
Hold buckle and pull top strap for a tight fit. Please keep your seat
belt fastened at all times while in your seat.
FLOTATION
CUSHIONS
1. Lift up at rear
of cushion
Push down on
front to unhook
3. Use straps
for holding
The cushion you are seated on will float. In water landing
remove
your cushion
as shown in diagram and take it with you in leaving
the aircraft.
PORTABLE ELECTRONIC DEVICES
Federal Aviation Agency (FAA) regulation prohibits the operation in-
flight of certain portable electronic devices since they can interfere
with the aircraft's navigation system.
Please
check with the Flight
Attendant before operating your radio, dictating machine or recorder.
